Male - abdominal tergal cleft. Anterior portion V-shaped with slight inward medial swelling but lacking crenulations along inner margins, anterior terminus very narrowly rounded (Figs 3
A-D
). Posterior portion slightly more U-shaped with several irregularly-sized and rounded teeth projecting medially.

Male - epiproct. Triangular base narrowing to anteriorly-recurved and tapering terminal spine, no accessory spine or swelling present (Figs 3
E-H
). Conspicuous tubercles located on the anterior margins of the triangular base. No accessory spine or cusp present.

USA: AL, AR, IL, IN, KS, KY, MO, OK, OH, TN, TX, WV (
DeWalt et al. 2012
)
